- Management
  - Open a freenode IRC channel
  - Publish a live distro with Ardesia
  - Define minimum system requirements
  - Make a pdf user manual
  - Make a video tutorial
  - Ardesia fedora packaging

  
- Bug fix:
  - Fix the wrong position of the text cursor on windows
  - Fix the highlighter; this doesn't work under Windows
    because seems that the ARGB32 support in cairo is not yet available 
	
	
- MacOsX-quartz porting
  - Investigate about the status and make a plan


- Reengineering
  - gui and icon revision to increase the usability
  - Reduce the video size
  - Screencast recorder using vlclib instead spawn the vlc process
  - Code revision
  - Bar and transparent layer on the same window
  - Store and load the savepoints using svg files
  - cache in memory the recent savepoint; in this way we'll have 
    a more reactive undo/redo
  - more compact savepoint storage
  - email integration without spawn the xdg-email script 
  - better integration with the florence virtual keyboard
  - better integration with the Tablet PC Input Panel
  - Better polygon recognition and drawing
  - reduce the white blinking when the windows are opened


- Windows operating systems
  - audio recording without configure the sound card name inside
    the screencast.bat
  - avoid to add the vlc.exe to PATH environment variable
  - Create a binary installer similar to the gimp Windows installer 
    http://gimp-win.sourceforge.net/
  - Windows Xp support
  - Build a 64 bit executable version


- Candidate features:
  - Deploy the artifact online
    - video; youtube upload
    - send saved images with email 
